<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-01-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="334" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                    <head>No. 334.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Anderson</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-01-08"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 8,
                            1888</date>.<lb/>(Received January 9—11.10 a.m.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Benson’s identity perfectly established. Prisoner will be delivered to United
                        States officer on his arrival here. Send officer at once.</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Anderson.</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>